This repository contains the code files associated with the arXiv preprint entitled: "Dirac fermions in non-Hermitian magnetic fields: Zero modes and index theorem"

Lattice and Operations python libraries are custom libraries which are needed for foundational operations like identifying nearest neighbors from a Hamiltonian, generating q=3 Hyperbolic lattices, etc. These dependencies are forzen state versions of an external repository found at the following URL:

https://github.com/CALeong/Personal_Minimal_Code_Package

See the above repository for any changes or updates to these libraries.

Any other dependencies that lie outside of the above libraries are contained in the ProjectSpecific library, which namely contains dependencies for generating the type-I and type-II non-Hermitian magnetic field Hamiltonians on honeycomb nanoribbon and hyperbolic q=3 lattices.

For the specific codes used to generate the figures in the arXiv preprint, which utilize the above dependencies, see the Run_Template_Scripts directory.

